        <h2>Common Issues with Electro Freeze Ice Cream Machines</h2>
        <p>Over time, Electro Freeze ice cream machines can develop various issues that require professional attention. Some of the most common problems include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ice cream not freezing properly</strong> – Caused by refrigerant leaks, compressor issues, or a faulty thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Machine making excessive noise</strong> – Could be due to worn-out bearings, motor issues, or loose internal components.</li>
            <li><strong>Low ice cream output</strong> – May result from clogged mix lines, improper calibration, or a failing auger motor.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice cream consistency problems</strong> – Often caused by incorrect viscosity settings or malfunctioning sensors.</li>
            <li><strong>Electrical failures</strong> – Faulty wiring, blown fuses, or control board malfunctions can lead to power issues.</li>
        </ul>
        
